sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh<br/>Payload Logger
    participant KS as KServe<br/>Inference Logger
    participant Consumer as TrustyAI<br/>ConsumerEndpoint<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CloudEvt as TrustyAI<br/>CloudEventConsumer<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant MMRecon as ModelMesh<br/>PayloadReconciler
    participant KSRecon as KServe<br/>PayloadReconciler
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC/MinIO/DB)
    participant Scheduler as Prometheus<br/>Scheduler<br/>(cron 5s)
    participant Fairness as Fairness Engine<br/>(SPD, DIR)
    participant Drift as Drift Engine<br/>(KS, FourierMMD)
    participant Publisher as Prometheus<br/>Publisher
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>Server
    participant Client as API Client
    participant Explainer as Explainer Engine<br/>(LIME, SHAP, CF)
    participant ModelSrv as KServe<br/>Model Server

    Note over MM,Storage: Flow 1: ModelMesh Inference Data Ingestion
    MM->>Consumer: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP (no TLS)
    Consumer->>MMRecon: Partial payload (input or output)
    Note right of MMRecon: Matches request/response<br/>pairs by inference ID<br/>(strips __isvc suffix)
    MMRecon->>Storage: Store matched record<br/>(PVC: File I/O | MinIO: HTTP | DB: JDBC)

    Note over KS,Storage: Flow 2: KServe CloudEvent Inference Data Ingestion
    KS->>CloudEvt: CloudEvent POST<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP (no TLS)
    CloudEvt->>KSRecon: Partial payload (request or response)
    Note right of KSRecon: Matches request/response<br/>pairs by inference ID
    KSRecon->>Storage: Store matched record

    Note over Scheduler,Prom: Flow 3: Scheduled Metric Computation & Prometheus Publication
    Scheduler->>Storage: Read inference data
    Storage-->>Scheduler: Dataframes
    Scheduler->>Fairness: Compute SPD, DIR
    Fairness-->>Scheduler: Metric values
    Scheduler->>Drift: Compute KS, FourierMMD, Meanshift
    Drift-->>Scheduler: Metric values
    Scheduler->>Publisher: Publish as Prometheus gauges<br/>(trustyai_ prefix)
    Prom->>Consumer: GET /q/metrics<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    Consumer-->>Prom: Prometheus text format

    Note over Client,ModelSrv: Flow 4: Explainer Prediction (disabled in RHOAI)
    Client->>Consumer: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    Consumer->>Explainer: Explanation request
    loop Multiple prediction calls (Semaphore: max 5)
        Explainer->>ModelSrv: gRPC inference request<br/>(plaintext, per-request channel)
        ModelSrv-->>Explainer: Prediction response
    end
    Explainer-->>Consumer: Explanation result<br/>(feature importances)
    Consumer-->>Client: JSON response

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 5: Data Upload (with gzip support)
    Client->>Consumer: POST /data/upload<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP<br/>(Content-Encoding: gzip)
    Note right of Consumer: GzipRequestFilter<br/>decompresses payload
    Consumer->>Storage: Store batch data<br/>+ ground truth labels
    Storage-->>Consumer: Confirmation
    Consumer-->>Client: 200 OK

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 6: Metric Scheduling via API
    Client->>Consumer: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd/request<br/>Schedule recurring SPD
    Consumer->>Scheduler: Register metric computation<br/>(model, protected attr, thresholds)
    Note right of Scheduler: Recalculated each cycle<br/>SPD threshold: -0.1 to 0.1<br/>DIR threshold: 0.8 to 1.2
    Scheduler-->>Consumer: Confirmation
    Consumer-->>Client: 200 OK
